    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I need to uninstall and reinstall the keyboard drivers. I'll need admin for this too. Let me write a script that:\n1. Uninstalls the keyboard devices (so they get re-detected)\n2. Scans for hardware changes to re-detect them\n3. Installs fresh drivers",
      "timestamp": 1782378985045
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"$logFile = \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\opencode\\\\reinstall-log.txt\\\"\\n\\\"Starting driver reinstall at $(Get-Date)\\\" | Out-File $logFile\\n\\\"Admin: $([Security.Principal.WindowsPrincipal][Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()).IsInRole([Security.Principal.WindowsBuiltInRole]::Administrator)\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 1: Uninstall the current keyboard devices so they get re-detected with fresh drivers\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 1: Uninstalling keyboard devices ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n$keyboards = @(\\n    \\\"ACPI\\\\HPQ8001\\\\4&34B2E6AD&0\\\",\\n    \\\"HID\\\\VID_045E&PID_07F8&MI_00\\\\7&22995292&0&0000\\\"\\n)\\n\\nforeach ($kb in $keyboards) {\\n    \\\"Uninstalling: $kb\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n    $output = & pnputil /remove-device \\\"$kb\\\" 2>&1\\n    $output | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n    \\\"Exit: $LASTEXITCODE\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n}\\n\\n# Step 2: Scan for hardware changes to re-detect keyboards\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 2: Scanning for hardware changes ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 2\\n$scanOutput = & pnputil /scan-devices 2>&1\\n$scanOutput | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 3: Verify\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 3: Verifying ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 3\\n$kbList = & pnputil /enum-devices /class Keyboard 2>&1\\n$kbList | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 4: Restart keyboard services\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 4: Restarting services ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nRestart-Service -Name kbdhid -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"kbdhid restarted: $?\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nRestart-Service -Name i8042prt -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"i8042prt restarted: $?\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n\\\"Done at $(Get-Date)\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\opencode\\\\reinstall-drivers.ps1\"}",
      "output": "Wrote file successfully.",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1782378992931
    },
    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Wait - I need to be careful not to kill your laptop keyboard. Let me revise this to be safer.",
      "timestamp": 1782378993004
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Wait, I should be careful here. Uninstalling the PS/2 keyboard could be risky - if the laptop keyboard is the only input and we uninstall it, the user could lose keyboard input entirely. The PS/2 keyboard is the internal laptop keyboard (ACPI\\HPQ8001). If I remove it, the user won't have any keyboard until the reboot or hardware scan picks it back up.\n\nActually, the USB keyboard (Microsoft) is the external one. The PS/2 one is the internal laptop keyboard. Let me be more careful:\n\n1. Only uninstall the USB keyboard and re-detect it\n2. Keep the PS/2 keyboard running\n3. Restart the services to refresh them\n\nActually, a better approach is to NOT uninstall the running devices. Instead:\n- Remove the stale driver packages \n- Reset the services\n- Force a driver reinstall on the existing devices\n\nLet me revise the approach to be safer.",
      "timestamp": 1782378995092
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"$logFile = \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\opencode\\\\reinstall-log.txt\\\"\\n\\\"Starting keyboard driver refresh at $(Get-Date)\\\" | Out-File $logFile\\n\\\"Admin: $([Security.Principal.WindowsPrincipal][Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()).IsInRole([Security.Principal.WindowsBuiltInRole]::Administrator)\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 1: Force reinstall drivers using pnputil /scan-devices and driver refresh\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 1: Refreshing keyboard drivers ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Scan for changes\\n$scanOutput = & pnputil /scan-devices 2>&1\\n$scanOutput | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 2: Restart keyboard services\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 2: Restarting keyboard services ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n\\\"Stopping kbdhid...\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nStop-Service -Name kbdhid -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"kbdhid stopped\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n\\\"Stopping mouclass...\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append  \\nStop-Service -Name mouclass -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"mouclass stopped\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 2\\n\\n\\\"Starting mouclass...\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nStart-Service -Name mouclass -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"mouclass started\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n\\\"Starting kbdhid...\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nStart-Service -Name kbdhid -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"kbdhid started\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n\\\"Starting mouhid...\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\nStart-Service -Name mouhid -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n\\\"mouhid started\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 3: Clean up old driver store packages (stale keyboard drivers)\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 3: Listing old driver packages ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n$oldDrivers = & pnputil /enum-drivers 2>&1\\n$oldDrivers | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n# Step 4: Verify keyboard state\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== Step 4: Final verification ===\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n$kbList = & pnputil /enum-devices /class Keyboard 2>&1\\n$kbList | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n$services = Get-Service kbdhid, i8042prt, mouhid, mouclass -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\\n$services | Format-Table Name, Status, StartType | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\\n\\\"Done at $(Get-Date)\\\" | Out-File $logFile -Append\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\opencode\\\\reinstall-drivers.ps1\"}",
      "output": "Wrote file successfully.",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1782379004092
    },
