    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Done. Here's the summary:\n\n## What was fixed\n\n**Removed 18 phantom/ghost keyboard devices** -- stale entries from old keyboards (Lenovo, Primax, old Microsoft instances) that were causing conflicts.\n\n**Restarted all keyboard services** -- `kbdhid`, `i8042prt`, `mouclass`, `mouhid` are all now Running.\n\n## Current state -- clean\n\n| Device | Status |\n|--------|--------|\n| HP PS/2 Keyboard (internal laptop) | OK |\n| Microsoft USB Keyboard (`VID_045E`) | OK |\n\n| Service | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| `i8042prt` | Running |\n| `kbdhid` | Running |\n| `mouclass` | Running |\n| `mouhid` | Running (was stopped before) |\n\n## Recommended next step\n\nYour **BIOS is outdated** (F.24 from 2021). HP has released updates for the OMEN 15-ce0xx that fix USB/keyboard initialization at boot. Update it via HP Support Assistant or from [HP's driver page](https://support.hp.com) to prevent boot-time keyboard issues.",
      "timestamp": 1782379044460
