    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "That sounds like **Toggle Keys** or **Filter Keys** accessibility features are turned on. Let me check and fix those settings.",
      "timestamp": 1782379185909
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is saying that when they press keys, it just makes noises. This could be several things:\n\n1. Sticky keys or filter keys are enabled (accessibility features)\n2. Toggle keys are enabled (makes a sound when Caps Lock, Num Lock, or Scroll Lock is toggled)\n3. Sound settings are causing auditory feedback for key presses\n4. Some accessibility feature is turned on\n\nLet me check the accessibility settings for keyboard - specifically ToggleKeys, FilterKeys, and StickyKeys.",
      "timestamp": 1782379188512
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-ItemProperty -Path \\\"HKCU:\\\\Control Panel\\\\Accessibility\\\\KeyboardResponse\\\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Format-List\", \"description\": \"Check FilterKeys settings\"}",
      "output": "(no output)",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1782379191242
    },
