      "text": "The \"Keyboard Response\" (which is FilterKeys) has Flags: 0, which means it's disabled too. \n\nThe \"HighContrast\" has Flags: 126. Let me check what that means:\n126 = 64+32+16+8+4+2 = 0b01111110\n- Bit 1 (0x02) = High Contrast is ON\n\nWait, actually the path shown is \"Keyboard Response\" not \"HighContrast\" - let me look again. The output shows:\n\n```\nPSChildName            : Keyboard Response\n...\nFlags                  : 0\n```\n\nThen at the end:\n```\nFlags : 126\n```\n\nThat last `Flags: 126` is from HighContrast. Let me check that. Actually, High Contrast being enabled would make things look different but wouldn't cause keyboard noises. \n\nThe main issue was ToggleKeys (Flags: 62 -> now 0) and StickyKeys (Flags: 510 -> now 0). Both are now disabled.\n\nLet me also check if the system beep is enabled somewhere.",
