    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I need a bit more info to narrow this down. Can you describe the noises?\n\n- **Crackling/popping** (intermittent snaps)\n- **Buzzing/humming** (constant low-frequency)\n- **Static/white noise** (hissing)\n- **Distorted/garbled audio** (like a broken speaker)\n- **Feedback loop** (squealing/screeching)\n\nIn the meantime, here's what I've found so far:\n\n## Audio stack overview\n\n| Device | Status |\n|--------|--------|\n| Realtek HD Audio (main speakers) | OK |\n| Intel HDMI Audio (display output) | OK |\n| NVIDIA Virtual Audio (screen recording) | OK |\n| **FxSound Audio Enhancer** | OK -- **running, 98.5% CPU usage** |\n| Andrea Comm USB-SA Headset | Phantom (disconnected) |\n\n## Key finding: **FxSound is consuming 98.5% CPU**\n\n`FxSound.exe` is an audio post-processing enhancer from 2022 (v1.1.15). It sits between all audio output and your speakers, applying effects like equalizer, surround sound, and volume boost. A CPU-hogging audio enhancer is a prime suspect for weird speaker noises -- it could be:\n\n- **Distorting audio** from over-processing\n- **Introducing latency artifacts** causing crackling\n- **Conflicting with the Realtek effects** (you have both enabled)\n\nThe FxSound version is also very old (March 2022) with an auto-updater checking every 2 days.",
      "timestamp": 1782380211453
    },
