      "type": "thought",
      "text": "So now I can see that the FxSound *driver is NOT showing up in the standard device list. However, it's still present in the Root\\\\MEDIA device:\n\n`ROOT\\MEDIA\\0000` - FxSound Audio Enhancer - Driver: oem125.inf\n\nAnd the PnP driver shows:\n- DeviceName: Speaker/Headphone (FxSound Audio Enhancer)\n- DriverVersion: 10.0.19041.1\n- DriverDate: 06/12/2019\n\nThis indicates that there are TWO entries - one is the actual driver (FXVAD) and another is the audio enhancer device interface.\n\nLet me get more detailed information about the FXVAD driver.\n\nAlso, I notice the user wants to keep FxSound because they listen to a lot of tech stuff and Zoom meetings - which makes sense. They need it to be properly configured, not removed entirely.\n\nLet me provide them with specific options for cleaning up the problematic parts while keeping the benefits.",
