      "text": "Done. Here's the full summary of everything that was fixed across both sessions:\n\n---\n\n## Session 1: Keyboard Issues\n\n### What was wrong\n- **StickyKeys** (Flags=510) and **FilterKeys** (Flags=127) were ON in live memory, causing beeping noises on every keypress\n- **18 phantom/ghost keyboard devices** from old keyboards (Lenovo, Primax, old Microsoft) were cluttering the device tree\n- Registry showed 0 but live memory state was different (sticky keys activated via shortcut Shift x5, FilterKeys via hold Right Shift 8 sec)\n\n### What was fixed\n- Killed all accessibility beeping via `SystemParametersInfo` API\n- Removed all 18 phantom keyboard devices\n- Restarted all keyboard services (`kbdhid`, `i8042prt`, `mouhid`, `mouclass`)\n- Final state: 2 clean keyboards, all services running\n\n---\n\n## Session 2: Audio Crackling\n\n### What was wrong\n- **FxSound FXVAD driver** (v14.1.0, from 2021) was stuck in the kernel, consuming **100% CPU**\n- **Andrea USB headset** was a phantom device causing audio routing confusion\n- The aged FXVAD driver conflicted with Realtek's audio pipeline, causing crackling\n\n### What was fixed\n- Removed phantom **Andrea USB headset** device\n- Removed **FxSound Audio Enhancer** phantom device (`ROOT\\MEDIA\\0000`)\n- Uninstalled and deleted the **FXVAD driver** (`oem125.inf`)\n- Relaunched FxSound cleanly with Voice preset for Zoom\n- FxSound now runs at **0.15 CPU** (was 100%)\n\n### Final audio device state\n| Device | Status |\n|--------|--------|\n| Realtek HD Audio | OK |\n| Intel HDMI Audio | OK |\n| NVIDIA Virtual Audio | OK |\n| Andrea headset | Removed |\n| FXVAD/FxSound phantom | Removed |\n\n---\n\n**Test your audio in Zoom now.** The crackling should be gone. FxSound is running with the \"Voice\" preset which is optimized for calls and meetings.",
